* Potions<br>
* Disarm/Sense Traps (very rarely needed)<br>
* .... <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#112512><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub16.ezboard.com/bdruzzilro86846.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=xhanjira>xhanjira</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Newbie</span><br>  Posts: 4<br> <font color=#CCCCC8>(6/1/01 7:36:44 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Fair donation for a corpse drag or lock pick?</span><hr size=1> I've been asked by several people on many occasions to summon or pull corpses out of sticky places.  Each time, the coffin in question was either provided, or they ported me back to Neriak and gave me the pp to purchase them.  One thing that most people don't understand is that the summon corpse spell uses quite a bit of mana for me at lvl 48 approx 2 full bulbs (with 202int and mana items) so the spell is quite costly for me..also costs me 700 mana to cast the spell and no, mana regen isn't quick for me without breeze or clarity....<br>
<br>
The one most recent was for someone in the Wakening Lands..had never been there before and they provided me an escort through Kael as well as the coffins.  A donation wasn't asked for as I was in the Great Divide anyhow, but was given.  The person I summoned was a chanter and was kind enough to give me clarity for my troubles as well...They had lost their level and I spent most of my night with them until they had gotten their level back..as a result of my kindness, once again I had gotten an unexpected reward..<br>
<br>
I still remember the day I first got my summon corpse spell and was asked by a high lvl druid to do a corpse recovery in lower guk.  As a result, I was rewarded with a high lvl necro spell and they made sure I was escorted down to the dungeon as I had never been in there before..<br>
<br>
I've had other occasions where people demand that I drop what I am doing to either summon their corpse or to recover it for them since I'm a necro and I have invis and IVU.  It's the ones that demand that I tend to ignore.  If my friend's cleric is nearby, often I give a free rez to the people whose corpse I summoned or retrieved.<br>
<br>
As for Rogues..personally, I love them...and I'm sure as I get higher lvl my appreciation for their skills will increase.  The few times I've needed help with a body recovery I've donated quite well....and I have to admit, it's nice to have assistance on corpse recoveries :-)  especially in bad zones...<br>
<br>
End point..be kind to whomever you ask and donate..I'd rather see an attempt at a donation than nothing at all..even a simple &quot;thank you&quot; works for those that can't afford it...Those that ask nicely, even if I'm on the other side of the world, sure I'll help if I'm able..just don't make demands or threats...I'm actually looking forward to that upgraded corpse summon spell and those stackable coffins..at least then I can keep one or two on me conveniently.<br>
<br>
So yes, there are a lot of demanding people on the server..but then again..there are some that are very kind and generous....I donate well for ports, translocations and even rez'es when needed..If I am in a group and my groupmates die, I'm one of the first looking for a cleric to rez...I'll help if I can if asked nicely...be rude in how you ask, and I'll ignore you.<br>
<br>
