<br>
*waves at Ashwood*  Thanks again for getting our 'fearless leader' out of HS   *mumbles about silly dwarves* <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#112512><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub16.ezboard.com/useaindarkseraph.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Seain DarkSeraph</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Newbie</span><br>  Posts: 18<br> <font color=#CCCCC8>(6/21/01 12:55:32 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Inequity of Perception</span><hr size=1> As a rule, I never charge nor accept payment for corpse retrievals.  its not in my 'character' to do so, so I offer them as a valorous act.<br>
<br>
This is not to say -however- that Rogue skills do deserve to be rewardable.  I simply forgoe it as an extension of my characterization of my rogue.<br>
<br>
The one thing that DOES disturb my in the inequity of perception that surrounds Rogues and their skills and how that compares to Druids, specifically.<br>
<br>
Druids expect and are largely granted to ability to charge -often exhorbitant- prices for ports.  While I admit that druids MUST pay for their spells, this does not fully reconcile the charges that some ask.  Or, let me rephrase this:<br>
<br>
Publically, it is 'acceptable' for a druid to ask for money in exchange for services.  Everyone expects and accepts this activity.  But if a rogue asks for services rendered, such as CR or door opening, the jaws drop in astonishment.  Why are rogues different?  Why are our skills devalued to the point of being 'free'?<br>
<br>
yes, druids pay for their spells, but Rogues pay for their skills, both in time and blood.  Porting to EC or LS or some such place is rarely a dangerous act.  yes, it cost Druid X the money to buy the spell and time to perfect their skills as casting it, but a druid rarely dies porting to NK.  The same cannot be aid for the rogue who does a CR into LGuk.<br>
<br>
Now, let me clarify what I'm saying for the Johnny Blazes out there: I believe druids deserve recompense for services rendered, but i also feel that same standard holds true for any class that renders a specific service be they rogue, Necro, Wizards.  Hell, if you 'hire' a 50 Warrior to go destroy CB so you can get your corpse in the tower, he deserevs some cash too.<br>
<br>
<br>
I hear a lot of arguments from my guild's rogues that people say rogue skills are not worth the money.  My response to that is that when you are in your 50s and you're standing at the door that lies between you and about 3 bubs of lost experience, tell me how valuable my ability to open that door is. <p><small><i>Venerato Quod Equitas</i>,
